==Trivia==
*In the comics, Black Bolt is a member of the [[Illuminati]], a group made of the smartest and most powerful characters in the Marvel Universe, including [[Stephen Strange]], [[Tony Stark]], [[T'Challa]] and [[Namor]].
*In the final scene of ''[[...And Finally: Black Bolt]]'', Black Bolt's uniform is a reference to the classic costume from the comics, with the cape referencing his wings.
*Black Bolt's crown is a reference to his [[Black Bolt's Helmet|original mask]] from the comics.
*With [[Black Bolt/Earth-838|Black Bolt]] from an alternate universe appearing as one of the members of the [[Illuminati]] in ''[[Doctor Strange in the Multiverse of Madness]]'', Black Bolt is the first [[Marvel Cinematic Universe]] character introduced in ''[[Inhumans (TV series)|Inhumans]]'' to subsequently appear in a [[Marvel Studios]] production.

==Behind the Scenes==
*[[Vin Diesel]] was linked to the role of Black Bolt for a long time when ''[[Inhumans (film)|Inhumans]]'' was being developed as a feature film.<ref>[https://www.facebook.com/jgunn/posts/10153768720331157?comment_id=10153768728991157&reply_comment_id=10153768755216157 James Gunn on Facebook - November 17, 2016]</ref>
*For ''[[Inhumans (TV series)|Inhumans]]'', [[Anson Mount]] created a new sign language for Black Bolt, since he was not from Earth and would not know ASL.<ref>[https://sciencefiction.com/2017/05/09/anson-mount-created-a-new-sign-language-for-black-bolt-in-marvels-inhumans/ Anson Mount Created A New Sign Language For Black Bolt In Marvel's 'Inhumans]</ref>
*[[Antal Kalik]] and [[Todd Sells]] were stunt doubles for [[Anson Mount]] in the role of Black Bolt.

